properties.areaDesc: East Slopes of the Washington Cascades
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 1:38AM PST until February 8 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...WINTER STORM TO BRING IMPACTFUL SNOW TO AREA MOUNTAINS THROUGH
SATURDAY EVENING...

.A vigorous winter storm will move into the area today. A cold
front will lower snow levels leading to significant snow
accumulations for the Washington Cascades and Blue Mountains of
Oregon and Washington today and tonight.

* WHAT...Snow. The snow may become heavy at times. Total snow
accumulations of 3 to 5 inches, but 6 to 12 inches near the
Cascade crest.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the Washington Cascades.

* WHEN...Through 10 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Gusting winds will
create drifting and blowing of snow reducing visibilities at
times.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Stay tuned to NOAA weather radio...social media for additional
updates.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
